  <text>
    <body>
      <p>
        <s>The <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="scene">7th scene of the first act</ref> of <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="author"><choice><orig>Shakespears</orig><reg>Shakespeare's</reg></choice></ref> drama <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="title">Macbeth</ref> is about <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character"><choice><orig>Macbeths</orig><reg>Macbeth's</reg></choice></ref> and <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character"><choice><orig>Lady Macbeths</orig><reg>Lady Macbeth's</reg></choice></ref> plan to kill <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character">King Duncan</ref>.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>After a battle against the <choice><orig>irish</orig><reg>Irish</reg></choice>, <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character">Macbeth</ref> meets <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character">three witches</ref>, who prophesy him his future as King of <name type="geo">Scotland</name> and <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character">Thane of Cawdor</ref>.</s>
        <s>Shortly thereafter he is awarded the title of <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character">Thane of Cawdor</ref> and goes to prepare a banquet in honor of <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character">King Duncan</ref> during which this scene takes place.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>After <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character">Macbeth</ref> leaves the chamber, <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character">Lady Macbeth</ref> meets him there in order to ask him why he left.</s>
        <s>Outside they both discuss <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character"><choice><orig>Macbeths</orig><reg>Macbeth's</reg></choice></ref> lack of ambition in killing the King.</s>
        <s>After a lot of convincing, <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character">Lady Macbeth</ref> wins <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character">Macbeth</ref> over for her plan to kill the King in order to fulfill <ref target="c12gk2_1" type="character"><choice><orig>Macbeths</orig><reg>Macbeth's</reg></choice></ref> desire to become King of <name type="geo">Scotland</name> himself.</s>
      </p>
